reviews.text: Clean, organised, informations about arrivals and departures visible,  staff on site very helpful and friendly,  sheltered areas, coffee machine,  snacks and pop machine available. Coffee room closed after 17:00.

Shipley is a nice town to visit with hills in the background. The station is a triangle where four train services exchange passengers. They are, 1 Leeds to Bradford, 2 Leeds to Skipton, 3 Bradford to Ilkley, 4 Bradford to Skipton. There is a ticket and information office.
An attractive triangular railway station. The only one of it's kind left.
Strange station as there are platforms on 3 seperate sides with the car park and station building in the middle. Lots of trains to bradford and Leeds
Great station with very frequent reliable services. Parking is a nightmare but aside from that the staff are friendly.
